  <amendments/>
  <summary>2/9/1987--Introduced.
Amends the Omnibus Crime Control and Safe Streets Act to increase from $50,000 to $100,000 the amount of benefits paid to public safety officers (law enforcement officers and fire fighters) who die as a result of an injury sustained in the line of duty. Removes the requirement that parents be dependents of the deceased in order to receive such benefits.</summary>
